txt.en: Investigate sea-hawk nests in the north and see if you can find any curios or oddities. Return any that you find to Luthana at the expedition encampment.
Collect dirt-encrusted baubles from sea-hawk nests ([placeholder]/14)
Luthana requested that you search for sea-hawk nests far to the north for baubles and trinkets stolen from shipwrecks. She will use the baubles to satisfy her patrons in Umbar Baharbêl.

'Go north beyond the city of Umbar into the hills that meet the shore. Examine sea-hawk nests for signs of baubles or keepsakes and collect them. Return anything you find to me, and I will reward you for what you discover.'

'Go north beyond the city of Umbar into the hills that meet the shore. Examine sea-hawk nests for signs of baubles or keepsakes and collect them. Return anything you find to me, and I will reward you for what you discover.'
You collected enough baubles to satisfy Luthana's patrons in Umbar Baharbêl. Deliver the baubles to her at the expedition camp in the south-eastern area of the Cape of Umbar.
Collect dirt-encrusted baubles from sea-hawk nests ([placeholder]/14)
Deliver the baubles to Luthana at the hunter's expedition

'I will clean these items and separate those with value for shipment to the city's jewellers. I want to thank you for doing this. This effort is above and beyond what I am required to do. It earns me favour with the guild and the Kindred. This effort provides favour to the people of Umbar for you.'
Deliver the baubles to Luthana at the hunter's expedition
Jewellers purchase baubles found from sea-wrecks gathered by the sea-hawks that collect the shiny objects for their nests. Collect some of the dirty baubles for Luthana.

'Sea-hawks scavenge shore and shoals for materials to build their nests. The birds find baubles and curiosities within the wrecks along the sand bars to the north and store the treasures in their nests. Some of those baubles may have value to the jewellers in Umbar. Find encrusted keepsakes in the sea-hawk nests and return them to me here at the encampment.'
Deliver the dirt-encrusted baubles to Luthana at the expedition camp
